Yes. That is a real product concept, and it is strong.

Call it a Data Stock Market or Data Exchange:

People do not just hand over data for “free.”
They allocate their data to companies, models, or research pools the same way investors allocate capital to firms.

Core idea:
	•	Your data becomes an asset
	•	Companies compete to attract it
	•	You choose where to place it
	•	Returns come back to you based on what your data helps generate

The frame:

Money today:
	•	people invest dollars into companies
	•	companies use capital to produce value
	•	investors get upside

Your model:
	•	people invest data into companies
	•	companies use data to train, target, optimize, discover, or predict
	•	data contributors get upside

That is clean.

The primitive

A person has:
	•	identity
	•	consent
	•	datasets
	•	usage permissions
	•	risk preferences
	•	payout preferences

A company has:
	•	demand for certain data types
	•	models/pipelines that can monetize or learn from that data
	•	yield profiles
	•	trust/reputation score
	•	payout terms

The platform sits in the middle like an exchange.

