How value gets calculated

This is the hard part, but also the moat.

You need a contribution attribution engine.

Possible methods:
	•	equal pool split
	•	weighted by rarity
	•	weighted by quality
	•	weighted by verified impact
	•	weighted by ongoing utility over time
	•	weighted by exclusivity
	•	weighted by freshness/recency

So not all data is worth the same.

Examples:
	•	common browsing data = low yield
	•	verified medical outcomes = high yield
	•	expert-labeled edge cases for AI = very high yield
	•	geographically rare or temporally rare data = premium

So the platform would need a pricing model that estimates:
marginal contribution of each data stream to downstream value

That is basically the “P/E ratio” equivalent for data.

